## Sensitivity Calculation (mV/V)

Using FEM strain in a **half-bridge Wheatstone circuit**, the output voltage was approximated using:

\[
\frac{V_{out}}{V_{in}} \approx \frac{k (2\varepsilon)}{4}
\]

Where:

- \( k = \text{gauge factor} \approx 2.05 \)  
- \( \varepsilon = \text{longitudinal strain} \)  

### Final Sensitivity

\[
\boxed{V_{out}/V_{in} \ge 1.0\ \text{mV/V at 600 inÂ·lbf}}
\]

This satisfies the project requirement.

---

## Strain Gauge Selection

A commercially available gauge was selected based on geometry, sensitivity, and bonding-surface requirements.

### Selected Gauge

- **Model:** Vishay Micro-Measurements **EA-06-125BZ-350**  
- **Resistance:** 350 Î©  
- **Gauge Factor:** ~2.05  
- **Product Link:** https://www.micro-measurements.com  

### Gauge Specifications

| Parameter | Value |
|----------|--------|
| Grid Length | 3.18 mm (0.125 in) |
| Grid Width | 1.57 mm (0.062 in) |
| Pattern | Linear |

The gauge dimensions match the available bonding area and provide stable performance in the half-bridge configuration.

